Each one explores the same world differently.

---

Where I think emergence enters is that the world isn't completely specified.

Instead it defines constraints.

Different agents then traverse the possibility space.

Some discoveries become durable.

Some disappear.

That's a recognizable design pattern in many complex systems: specify the rules richly enough that interesting behavior emerges without prescribing every outcome.

