One thing I would probably add—not because it's missing, but because I think it fits—is the idea of **ecology**.

Not just daemons.

Not just operators.

An ecology.

Meaning every operator has:

* things it feeds on
* things it produces
* things it competes with
* things it cooperates with
* failure modes
* environmental conditions

Then the Pantheon isn't merely a collection of components.

It's an evolving ecosystem.

